rest_of_day_open: I see it going in much the same manner as usual. I expect to stay at home, to avoid the pandemic. I expect I will have a lot of housework, and hopefully more work online than usual. I expect I will be thinking a lot about the things I need to get done.
critical_positive: We had the same general opinions on most topics that were mentioned. I really liked that he was an animal lover, and although I'm really shy he was easy to talk to. He kept the conversation going at a good pace, and really was able to steer the conversation back when I ventured off topic, or was obviously uncomfortable.
critical_negative: The only thing that didn't work well was that it was hard to hear his mic. Also, I can be very shy, and I get obviously uncomfortable or embarrassed, which was entirely my own issue and he seemed to deal with it well. I think that it was easier due to his easy going manner.

rest_of_day_open: It's going to be a little rough. We don't have grocery money this month. Nothing to eat but noodles this weekend. Really hoping that it doesn't trigger a GERD attack in my Mom. This weekend will go bad fast if that happens. Worried about going to the emergency room during the pandemic. Just nothing but worries now that the expanded unemployment expired. Ever day is worse, really. This was a nice little break.
critical_positive: We're both animal lovers, so we were able to latch onto that immediately and talk about it for a while. Turned out that we are similarly liberal, too, so that also really gave us a lot to talk about. Honestly, I'm pretty sure that we could've kept talking easily for another hour. Nice girl. Easy to talk to.
critical_negative: The video was a little fuzzy on her end. I tried to make up for this by speaking loudly and clearly, but we ended talking over each other a little bit. Didn't really matter, though. We worked around it. It could've been a bigger problem if we didn't have a good report.
